    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Members of a genus containing two extant species of apes. The term "chimpanzees" properly refers to the genus and both or either species, however, it is sometimes used to refer to the species of common chimpanzee, Pan troglodytes.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
